      "title": "Customizing github blog",
      "permalink": "http://0.0.0.0:4321/blog-customizing/",
      "link": "http://0.0.0.0:4321/blog-customizing/",
      "date": "2019-02-25T00:00:00+00:00",
      
        "modified": "2019-02-26T08:15:52+00:00",
      
      "author": {
        "name": "Blankymunn",
        "url": null,
        "email": "trestucky@gmail.com"
      },
      "content": "<p>This post is for explanation about customizing my blog.</p>\n\n<p>After you cloned this blog, you can encounter tons of folders and files and probably get lost among them. So, I’m gonna explain what folder or file under ‘_app’ is for.<br /></p>\n\n<h1 id=\"1-assets\">1. Assets</h1>\n<div class=\"highlighter-rouge\"><div class=\"highlight\"><pre class=\"highlight\"><code>├── assets/\n|   └── _scss/\n|   |   └── _user.scss\n|   |   └── _variable.scss\n|   └── themes/curnata/\n|   |   └── _common.scss\n|\t|\t└── _variables.scss\n</code></pre></div></div>\n<p>The folder ‘Assets’ is consists of .scss files which contains classes and basic configs for the blog(e.g Blog’s color schemes, font-size, …).<br /></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"_scss_userscss\">_scss/_user.scss</h2>\n\n<p>This file contains user-make classes.<br />\nIf you wanna use your own classes, you can add yours to this file.</p>",
      "excerpt": "This post is for explanation about customizing my blog.",
      "languages": null,
      "categories": ["dev"],
      "tags": ["github"]
    }
    
  

  
